<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1546,2003]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis box="[151,273,1546,1571]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1546,1571]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Dark brown to black, subshiny; scutum with faint (but distinct in anterior view) black stripes between acrostichal and dorsocentral rows; 1 postsutural acrostichal; wing brown, broad; halter and legs yellow, posterior legs darker; mid and hind femora and tibiae flattened laterally, with peniform setae; female cercus short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1546,2003]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,375,1654,1679]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Re-description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[394,498,1655,1679]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Holotype</typeStatus>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[511,590,1654,1679]" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">female</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[765,859,1655,1679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
; wing 
<quantity box="[945,1039,1655,1679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
. Dichoptic; frons and face black, conspicuously grey pruinescent and slightly wider than ocellar tubercle, both twice as high as wide. Frons with 4 small proclinate setae. Ocellus glassy, yellow; anterior ocellar seta divergent, with 3–4 tiny posterior setae. Face bare, protuberant distally (
<figureCitation box="[462,551,1762,1786]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
). Postcranium (
<figureCitation box="[737,823,1762,1786]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black with grey pruinescence; with postocular setae uniserial, vertical setae more robust, 2 occipital setae directly posterior to vertical ones. Gena with longer, more numerous setae than postgena. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[802,889,1834,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
) velvety matte-black, finely grey pruinescent; postpedicel coniform, 1.5X longer than scape and pedicel combined, 3X longer than stylus. Proboscis 2X head height (
<figureCitation box="[236,319,1906,1930]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
); labrum brown on basal half, yellow on distal half; labium brown. Palpus hidden.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1546,2003]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,151,319]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="8" pageNumber="71">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[299,386,1943,1967]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="8" pageNumber="71">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black, except yellowish on margins of postpronotal lobe, postalar callus, scutellum and laterotergite; pruinescence greyish-brown on scutum and scutellum, light grey on notopleuron, postpronotal lobe and mesopleuron. Scutum with faint black longitudinal stripes between acrostichal and dorsocentral rows (
<figureCitation box="[376,464,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
), distinct in anterior view, slightly extending past transverse suture. Chaetotaxy: 5 distinct uniserial antepronotals; 1 robust, 3 weak postpronotals; 2 slender proepimerals; 1 postsutural acrostichal; 5 uniserial dorsocentrals; apparently no intra-alar; 1 presutural supra-alar; 1 shorter postsutural supra-alar; 3 robust, 2 tiny notopleurals; 1 postalar; 2 scutellars, apical pair longer, crossed; 12 laterotergitals.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="9" pageNumber="72" startId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" targetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1194,1310]" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">
