<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1354,2029]" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">
Legs yellow, hind pair darker, all grey pruinescent when seen in certain angles, more conspicuous on coxae. Foreleg (
<figureCitation box="[254,342,1390,1414]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
): tibia with row of short antero- and posterodorsal setae, slightly more robust than background setae; tarsomeres 1 and 2 with short, robust, setae medially and distally. Midleg (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1140,1426,1450]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
): femur and tibia flattened laterally; femur with dorsal and ventral peniform setae throughout length, dorsals shorter; tibia with peniform setae throughout dorsally and shorter ventrally at basal half; tibia with row of 4 antero- and posterodorsal setae, 1 longer anteroventral seta at middle, 2 shorter anteriors subapically. Hindleg (
<figureCitation box="[941,1027,1534,1558]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
): coxa shorter, thicker than fore and mid coxae; femur and tibia flattened laterally, both with long dorsal and ventral peniform setae along entire length, except on ventral distal fourth of tibia; femur with posteroventral row of small peniform setae, tibia with posterodorsal row of small peniform setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1354,2029]" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[279,363,1678,1702]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–85" captionStartId="15.[151,263,962,985]" captionTargetBox="[306,1281,194,941]" captionTargetId="figure-441@15.[306,1281,193,941]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 78–85. Wings. 78, Empis angustipennis Bezzi, lectotype ♀; 79, E. chiragra Bezzi, lectotype ♂; 80, E. induta Bezzi, female holotype; 81, E. leucostigma Bezzi, holotype ♀. 82, E. liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 83, E. lucidilabris Bezzi, ♀ from Peru; 84, E. penniventris Bezzi, holotype ♀. 85, E. spinifera Bezzi, lectotype ♂. Length of each wing informed along the text." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
) wide, with rounded apex, brown, with inconspicuous pterostigma; base of costal vein with robust seta (not represented in figure). Vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[662,670,1729,1743]" fontSize="6" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">1</subScript>
bare dorsally, slightly dilated towards apex. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1354,2029]" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Abdomen brown, subshiny, covered with small black setae, longer on posterior margin of tergites; grey pruinescent laterally on tergites. Sternites same color as tergites.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1354,2029]" pageId="9" pageNumber="72">
Terminalia with tergite 8 and sternite 8 of same length (
<figureCitation box="[859,947,1824,1848]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
); sternite 8 with apex projected ventrally; sternite 10 (
<figureCitation box="[285,368,1860,1884]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
) wider than tergite 10 (
<figureCitation box="[635,719,1860,1884]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
), with 2 paramedian sclerotized bands and short robust setae at base and thin setae at apex; genital fork triangular (
<figureCitation box="[720,804,1896,1920]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
); genital fork subtriangular (
<figureCitation box="[1122,1206,1896,1920]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
); cercus shorter than sternite 10 (
<figureCitation box="[284,418,1932,1956]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Figs. 47, 49</figureCitation>
) with robust marginal setae (
<figureCitation box="[744,882,1932,1956]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1194,1217]" captionTargetBox="[262,1330,392,1171]" captionTargetId="figure-453@9.[252,1336,373,1174]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. Empis liodes Bezzi, holotype ♀. 41, head, lateral view; 42, antenna, lateral view; 43; thorax, dorsal view; 44, right foreleg, posterior view; 45, right midleg, anterior view; 46, right hindleg, anterior view; 47, terminalia, lateral view; 48, terminalia, dorsal segments, dorsal view; 49, terminalia, ventral segments, ventral view. Abbreviations: GF = genital fork; St = sternite; T = tergites. Scales: Figures 44–46 = 1.0 mm; 41–43 = 0.5 mm; 47–49 = 0.2 mm." pageId="9" pageNumber="72">Figs. 48, 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
